        { "arabic": "اللُّغَةُ الْعَرَبِيَّةُ جَمِيلَةٌ", "english": "The Arabic language is beautiful" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Basic Formation Rules",
      "titleArabic": "قواعد التكوين الأساسية",
      "content": [
        "When the noun ends in ة, drop it before adding يّ: مَكَّة → مَكِّيّ, مَدِينَة → مَدَنِيّ.",
        "The kasra before يّ is part of the pattern: مِصْرِيّ (with kasra on ر)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Drop تاء مربوطة: مَكَّة → مَكِّيّ",
        "Noun ending in ـِيّ already: no change needed",
        "For cities: مَكَّة → مَكِّيّ، الْمَدِينَة → مَدَنِيّ",
        "The word takes regular adjective agreement"
